==English==
===Etymology===
Modern Latin, from Greek [[παραμηκης]] ‘oval’, from [[μηκος]] ‘length’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /pærə'mi:sɪəm/

===Noun===
'''paramecium''' (''plural'' '''paramecia''')
# a type of oval-shaped [[protozoan]] [[organism]]
#:*'''1997''': Edgar noticed that Clyde was wearing a necktie with a driblet deign.  The little figures made him think of '''paramecia''', sinister organisms with gullets and feeding grooves. — Don DeLillo, ''Underworld''